<task id="AUTHV2-049" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Rate limiting policies on anonymous + API key endpoints</title>
    <phase>C — Server hardening</phase>
    <tags>auth, server, rate-limiting, STANDARD</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>045</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>C-Parallel-2</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>RateLimitingModule is registered but no explicit policies on anonymous + API key endpoints. Add per-IP + per-user buckets for /api/registration/*, /api/v1/emails/webhook-trigger, /api/communications/incoming-webhook, /api/admin/builder-scope/import, /api/ai/rag/*.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET engineer.</role>
  <goal>Brute-force / DoS protection on all anonymous + API key endpoints. Reasonable limits (e.g., 100 req/min per IP for webhooks).</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/RateLimitingModule.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-AUTH-SYSTEM.md §3 M-? + customer-review §7.3</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Define rate-limit policies in RateLimitingModule: AnonymousWebhook (100/min per IP), Registration (20/hour per IP), ApiKey (1000/min per key), etc.</step>
    <step>Apply policies via `.RequireRateLimiting("AnonymousWebhook")` on affected endpoints.</step>
    <step>Test by hitting an endpoint above its limit and verifying 429 response.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Each affected endpoint has an explicit rate-limit policy.</criterion>
    <criterion>429 response with Retry-After header on excess.</criterion>
    <criterion>Legitimate traffic unaffected by reasonable limits.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
